command.name: Gesture
command.description: Parsed touch data as a gesture

variable.name: f1
variable.description: Indicates the number of intersection points between an input gesture g(x) and the straight line f(x) which connects the first and last point of the gesture

variable.name: f7
variable.description: Indicates the number of intersection points between an input gesture g(x) and all horizontal lines yi, where i is between 0 and n, that constitute a gesture

variable.name: f3
variable.description: Indicates the sign value of area gap between g(x) and f(x)

variable.name: f4
variable.description: Represents the sign value of the sum of the x coordinates of all the points that constitute strokes minus the x coordinates of the last point

variable.name: f5
variable.description: Checks the sign value of the sum of the x coordinates of all the points that constitute strokes minus x coordinates of the first point

variable.name: f6
variable.description: Indicates the sign value of the y coordinates of the last point minus y coordinates of the first point

variable.name: f8
variable.description: Checks whether or not x coordinates of all the points except for the first point and the last point is between x0 and xn

variable.name: f9
variable.description: Represents the sign value of the multiplication of x coordinates of the first point and the last point minus the mediate value of x coordinates of all the points

variable.name: f2
variable.description: Checks if the y coordinates of the points which exist between the intersection point and the last point are greater than the y coordinates of the intersection point

variable.name: OptionalPosition
variable.description: Option to set current value for position

command.name: setCounter
command.description: Set the counter value on the counter module
